sec.p:
Accuracy: The overall proportion of correctly classified instances across all classes.
\begin{equation*}
\text { Accuracy }=\frac{\text { Total Correct Predictions }}{\text { Total Predictions }}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

Precision: The proportion of correctly predicted positive instances out of all predicted positives, computed per class and averaged.
\begin{equation*}
\text { Precision }_{i}=\frac{T P_{i}}{T P_{i}+F P_{i}}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

Recall (also called Sensitivity or True Positive Rate): The proportion of correctly predicted positive instances out of all actual positives in each class.
\begin{equation*}
\operatorname{Recall}_{i}=\frac{T P_{i}}{T P_{i}+F N_{i}}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

F1-Score: The harmonic means of precision and recall, which balances both metrics.
\begin{equation*}
\mathrm{F} 1_{i}=2 \cdot \frac{\text { Precision }_{i} \cdot \text { Recall }_{i}}{\text { Precision }_{i}+\text { Recall }_{i}}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

Silhouette Score: Measures the compactness and separation of clusters based on intra-cluster vs. inter-cluster distances. A score close to 1 indicates well-separated and dense clusters.
\begin{equation*}
s=\frac{b-a}{\max (a, b)}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where $a$ is the average intra-cluster distance and $b$ is the nearestcluster distance.
